%h3 D. Protection of Tapjoy and Others:
%p
  We may release Personal Information when we believe in good faith that release is necessary to comply with the law; to enforce or apply our conditions of use and other agreements; or to protect the rights, property, or safety of Tapjoy, our employees, our users, or others. This includes exchanging Personal Information with other companies and organizations for fraud protection and credit risk reduction.

%h3 E. With Your Consent:
%p
  Except as set forth in A through D above, you will be notified when your Personal Information may be shared with third parties, and will be able to prevent the sharing of this information.

%h3 F. Facebook Connect and Other Social Features:
%p
  Tapjoy may allow users to use social features, such as Facebook Connect, offered by Facebook or other third-party social networking sites (“SNS”) to interact with friends. If you opt to use such a service, by proceeding, you are allowing Tapjoy to access certain of your information maintained by the SNS, and you are agreeing to the Terms of Use provided by that SNS.  By way of example, and depending on the privacy settings you have chosen at a given SNS, you might interact with friends who are also members of that SNS by automatically sharing your game reviews or other Tapjoy activity through the SNS (e.g., in the case of Facebook, by choosing to have your Tapjoy reviews automatically posted on your Timeline or choosing to use Facepile to post the Facebook profile pictures of users who have connected with your page), or by keeping up on your friends’ Tapjoy activity through their own automatic SNS account postings (e.g., on their updates shown on your Facebook Newsfeed).

%p
  If you are not currently registered with Tapjoy, you can use Facebook Connect to register; when you click on "Sign in Using Facebook", you will first be asked to enter your Facebook credentials and then be given the option to register and join Tapjoy. Once you register on Tapjoy and connect your Facebook credentials, you will be able to automatically post recent activity back to Facebook (i.e., on your Facebook Wall or Timeline). You have the option to disable Facebook Connect or similar SNS services at any time by logging into "My Profile" on your Tapjoy account and clicking on "Social Settings". You can also edit your privacy settings on the SNS itself (such as Facebook) to control the extent to which your activity on Tapjoy appears on Facebook, or to disconnect the Facebook Connect service, by visiting the Facebook Application Settings page.

%h2 IV. Is Personal Information About me Secure?
%p
  Your account is protected by a password for your privacy and security. You need to prevent unauthorized access to your account and Personal Information by selecting and protecting your password appropriately and limiting access to your computer and browser by signing off after you have finished accessing your account.

%p
  We endeavor to protect the privacy of your account and other Personal Information we hold in our records, but we cannot guarantee complete security. Unauthorized entry or use, hardware or software failure, and other factors, may compromise the security of user information at any time.

%p
  Tapjoy may contain links to other sites. We are not responsible for the privacy policies or practices of other sites. When following a link to another site you should read that site's privacy policy.


